title: Tie Me Kangaroo Down, Sport
lyrics: There's an old Australian Stockman lying, dying.
And he get's himself up onto one elbow
And he turns to his mates who are
all gathered around, and he says.
Ah, don't go away from the fool, Curl
And take me koala back, Jack
He lives somewhere out on the track, Mack
And mind me platypus duck, Bill
Ah, don't let 'em go runnin' a muck, Bill,
Ah, like keep playin' 'till I shoot
Tan me hide when I'm dead, Fred
Tan me hide when I'm dead.
So we tanned his hide when he died, Clyde
And that's it hangin' on the shed.
